From 03dd44ec7c6bcf0de80222090d8802bf6d276a51 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jul 2025 11:11:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd:Handle TPE PSD for punctured and 
 non-punctured 6 GHz channels

Update 'set_ieee_order_chan_list()' to retrieve the 6 GHz channel list
corresponding to the input client_type.
Previously, the function used the channel list index from
hostapd_channel_data, which contains a superset of all nine
6 GHz power mode channel lists. This list is not specific to any
client type. Modify the logic to fetch the appropriate channel list
for the given client_type, ensuring that the correct power mode and
associated power values are populated in the TPE IE.

Remove dependency on power values fetched via 'nl80211_get_reg' for
all 6 GHz power modes.
These values are no longer required, as all nine 6 GHz power mode
channel lists are now obtained using get_wiphy.

Update 'get_psd_for_chan_idx()' to retrieve PSD values for
both punctured and non-punctured channels based on the input channel index.

Introduce 'get_max_psd_for_composite_ap()' to modularize PSD retrieval logic.
This function is invoked for both puncturing and non-puncturing
scenarios to improve code clarity and reuse.

Update 'fill_psd_power_for_punctured_freq()' to align with regulatory guidance:
Set the regulatory PSD power for LPI-only punctured channels.
Set the PSD power to primary20MHZPSD - 16 dBm for SP punctured channels.

